# 🔌 TASK 6: Socket.IO – Real-Time Communication Layer

## 📖 Concept Overview

Socket.IO is a **real-time bidirectional communication framework** built on top of WebSockets and HTTP fallback mechanisms.

It ensures:
- Reliable data transmission
- Automatic reconnection
- Event-driven communication

## 🔹 Core Mechanisms

### Engine.IO Layer
- Handles transport negotiation.
- Falls back to HTTP polling if WebSocket fails.

### Message Buffering
- Stores events during temporary disconnection.
- Resends once connection restores.

### Namespaces & Rooms
- Logical separation of communication channels.
- Used in chat systems, multiplayer games, and dashboards.

