# 🌐 TASK 7: OSI Reference Model

## 📖 Concept Overview

The OSI (Open Systems Interconnection) Model standardizes network communication into **seven logical layers**.

Each layer has a defined responsibility:

1. Physical – Transmission of raw bits  
2. Data Link – Frame structure & MAC addressing  
3. Network – Routing & IP addressing  
4. Transport – Reliable data transfer (TCP/UDP)  
5. Session – Connection management  
6. Presentation – Encryption & formatting  
7. Application – User-level network services  

This abstraction allows:
- Interoperability across vendors
- Modular network troubleshooting
- Protocol standardization

