# 🔐 TASK 9: Encrypted Messaging System (E2EE)

## 📖 Concept Overview

This chat system implements **End-to-End Encryption (E2EE)** to ensure that only communicating users can read messages.

## 🔹 Key Generation

- PBKDF2 derives a secure 256-bit key.
- Uses 100,000 hashing iterations.
- Salt ensures uniqueness even with identical passwords.

## 🔹 Encryption Standard

AES-256-GCM provides:
- Confidentiality (encryption)
- Integrity (authentication tag)
- Protection against tampering

## 🔹 Initialization Vector (IV)

Each message:
- Uses a unique random IV.
- Ensures ciphertext randomness.
- Prevents pattern analysis attacks.

The server:
- Relays encrypted data only.
- Has no access to decryption keys.

